{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649963","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649963"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18386"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18386","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18386"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.18,0.08,0.75]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11104"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74439"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11104"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18386"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59930"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5795"},{"type":"tags","id":"6292"},{"type":"tags","id":"9222"},{"type":"tags","id":"11317"},{"type":"tags","id":"11318"},{"type":"tags","id":"11383"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25746"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25749"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74439","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74439"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following forms of treatment involves exposure of the fracture and arthrotomy of the joint to allow accurate reduction under direct vision?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Graft/substitute","Mobilisation of joint","Internal fixation","External fixation","Open reduction"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOpen reduction\u003C/strong\u003E involves surgically exposing the fracture site to allow for direct visualisation and accurate alignment of the bone fragments. This is often necessary for complex fractures, such as intra-articular fractures, where precise reduction is crucial to restore joint function and prevent long-term complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInternal fixation\u003C/strong\u003E typically follows open reduction and involves the use of hardware, such as plates and screws, to stabilise the fracture internally. While it is a common adjunct to open reduction, it is not the same as the initial exposure and reduction of the fracture.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal fixation\u003C/strong\u003E involves stabilising the fracture with a frame outside the body. It is often used when internal fixation is not feasible, such as in cases with significant soft tissue injury or infection risk. It does not involve direct exposure of the fracture site.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMobilisation of the joint\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the process of moving the joint to maintain or restore range of motion. It is not a method of fracture reduction or fixation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGraft/substitute\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the use of bone grafts or substitutes to fill bone defects or aid in healing. It is not directly related to the reduction of a fracture.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Open reduction involves surgically exposing a fracture to allow for direct visualisation and accurate alignment of the bone fragments.","Internal fixation is often used in conjunction with open reduction to stabilise the fracture with hardware such as plates, screws, or rods.","External fixation involves stabilising a fracture with a frame outside the body, typically used when internal fixation is not feasible."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59930"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18386"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59930"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T05:24:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T05:24:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11104"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74439"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"34","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/34"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","name":"Orthopaedics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"r